Barnier Sees ‘No Consensus’ in EU on Financial Transaction Tax

-- B y   J i m   B r u n s d e n
-- 
2011-09-17T10:12:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/barnier-sees-no-consensus-in-eu-on-financial-transaction-tax.html
Michel Barnier , the European
Union’s financial services commissioner, said there’s “no
consensus” in the bloc on introducting a financial-transaction
tax.  “There is no agreement in the EU” on the issue, Barnier
told reporters today after a meeting of EU finance ministers in
Wraclow,  Poland . “We are just starting debate on this.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
